HEADWORD: Jugum
<hw>Ju"gum</hw> <pr>(j⟦umac⟧"g⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> L. <plw>Juga</plw> <pr>(j⟦umac⟧"g⟦adot⟧)</pr>, E.
<plw>Jugums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a yoke, ridge.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of the ridges commonly found on
the fruit of umbelliferous plants.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A pair of the
opposite leaflets of a pinnate plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

